# Module Purpose

Responsibilities:

- Receive Provider Events
- Process Postbacks
- Process Webhooks
- Synchronize Order Data
- Trigger Commission Updates
- Ensure Idempotency

Webhooks are the primary integration point between Affiliate Providers and the platform.

---

# MVP Provider

Supported:

✓ Accesstrade

Future:

- Ecomobi
- MasOffer
- Other Providers

MVP must only implement Accesstrade.

Do not introduce multi-provider complexity.

---

# Core Flow

User

↓

Generate Affiliate Link

↓

Purchase Product

↓

Accesstrade Receives Conversion

↓

Accesstrade Sends Webhook

↓

Webhook Module

↓

Orders Module

↓

Cashback Processing

↓

User Balance Updated

---

# Architecture Rules

Webhook Module does NOT contain business logic.

Responsibilities:

✓ Validate Request

✓ Verify Signature

✓ Parse Payload

✓ Prevent Duplicates

✓ Dispatch Command

---

Business Logic belongs to:

Orders Module

Withdrawals Module

Application Layer

---

Bad

Webhook Controller

↓

Create Order

↓

Calculate Cashback

↓

Update Balance

---

Good

Webhook Controller

↓

Validate

↓

Dispatch Command

↓

Order Handler

↓

Business Logic

---

# Webhook Endpoint

Required Endpoint

POST

/api/v1/webhooks/accesstrade

Purpose:

Receive Accesstrade conversions.

---

No authentication required.

Must validate provider authenticity.

---

# Controller Rules

Webhook controller must remain thin.

Allowed:

- Validation
- Signature Verification
- Mapping DTO

Forbidden:

- Cashback Calculation
- Balance Updates
- Financial Logic

---

# Payload Rules

Create provider-specific DTO.

Example:

AccesstradeWebhookRequest

Never use dynamic objects.

Never use Dictionary<string, object>.

Payloads must be strongly typed.

---

# Signature Validation Rules

Critical Requirement

Every webhook must verify source authenticity.

---

Validation Methods

Preferred:

Provider Signature

Provider Secret

Provider Token

---

If signature invalid:

Return

```http
401 Unauthorized
```

---

Never process invalid payloads.

---

# Idempotency Rules

Most Important Rule

Webhook processing must be idempotent.

---

Example

Provider sends:

Order A

↓

Network Retry

↓

Order A Again

↓

No Duplicate Processing

---

Duplicate cashback is forbidden.

---

# Duplicate Detection Rules

Primary Key

ProviderOrderId

---

Optional

ProviderEventId

---

Store processed webhook events.

Suggested Entity:

WebhookEvent

Fields:

- Id
- Provider
- EventId
- ProviderOrderId
- Status
- Payload
- ReceivedAt
- ProcessedAt

---

Purpose:

Duplicate detection

Auditing

Troubleshooting

---

# Event Storage Rules

Every webhook event must be stored.

Even if processing fails.

Purpose:

Replay

Debugging

Auditing

---

Never discard incoming events.

---

# Processing Rules

Recommended Flow

Receive Event

↓

Validate Signature

↓

Store Event

↓

Check Duplicate

↓

Dispatch Command

↓

Update Event Status

---

# Event Status Rules

Use enum.

Examples:

Received

Processing

Processed

Failed

Ignored

---

Never delete webhook events.

---

# Failure Handling Rules

Failures must be recoverable.

Example

Webhook Received

↓

Database Failure

↓

Mark Failed

↓

Retry Later

---

Do not lose events.

---

# Retry Rules

Webhook processing must support retries.

---

Example

Failed

↓

Retry Job

↓

Success

↓

Processed

---

Retries must remain idempotent.

---

# Order Synchronization Rules

Webhook may:

Create Order

Update Order Status

Update Commission

---

Webhook must not:

Delete Orders

Delete Transactions

Delete Users

---

# Status Update Rules

Allowed

Pending

↓

Approved

---

Pending

↓

Rejected

---

Pending

↓

Cancelled

---

Approved

↓

Cancelled

(with reversal)

---

Approved

↓

Rejected

(with reversal)

---

All transitions must follow Orders Module rules.

---

# Financial Safety Rules

Balance changes only occur through Orders Module.

Webhook module must never:

- Update User Balance
- Create Withdrawal
- Modify Financial Transactions directly

---

Financial logic belongs elsewhere.

---

# Logging Rules

Log:

✓ Webhook Received

✓ Signature Validation Failure

✓ Duplicate Event

✓ Processing Success

✓ Processing Failure

---

Never log:

✗ Secrets

✗ Tokens

✗ Authorization Headers

---

Large payloads should be truncated.

---

# Security Rules

Whitelist provider IPs if supported.

Additional protection:

- Signature Validation
- Shared Secret
- Rate Limiting

---

Never trust:

- Request Body
- Query Parameters
- User-provided data

---

# Queue Processing Rules

Recommended Architecture

Webhook

↓

Queue

↓

Background Worker

↓

Process Command

---

Benefits

- Fast Response
- Retry Support
- Better Reliability

---

MVP Option

Direct Processing Allowed

Only if:

- Processing remains lightweight

---

Future Production

Queue is recommended.

---

# Monitoring Rules

Track:

- Webhooks Received
- Failed Events
- Duplicate Events
- Processing Time

---

Admin Dashboard should expose:

Webhook Health Metrics

